{"content":"---\ntitle: \"&lt;discoveryClientSettings&gt; | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.prod: \".net-framework\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"dotnet-clr\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\nms.assetid: 02e1b823-a8bb-4074-90d5-8599f71e8f9d\ncaps.latest.revision: 2\nauthor: \"Erikre\"\nms.author: \"erikre\"\nmanager: \"erikre\"\n---\n# &lt;discoveryClientSettings&gt;\nContains the settings needed by an application to participate in the service discovery process as a client.  \n  \n \\<system.ServiceModel>  \n\\<standardEndpoints>  \n  \n## Syntax  \n  \n```  \n  \n<system.serviceModel>  \n    <standardEndpoints>       <dynamicEndpoint>           <standardEndpoint>             <discoveryClientSettings discoveryEndpoint=\"String\" >               <findCriteria duration=\"TimeSpan\"                  maxResults=\"Integer\"                   scopeMatchBy=\"Uri\" >                  <contractTypeNames>                     <add name=\"String\" namespace=\"String\" />                  <contractTypeNames>                  <extensions />                  <scopes>                    <add scope=\"URI\"/>                  </scopes>               </findCriteria>             </discoveryClientSettings>          <standardEndpoint>       </dynamicEndpoint>            </standardEndpoints>  \n</system.serviceModel>  \n```  \n  \n## Attributes and Elements  \n The following sections describe attributes, child elements, and parent elements.  \n  \n### Attributes  \n  \n|Attribute|Description|  \n|---------------|-----------------|  \n|discoveryEndpoint|A string that contains the name of the Discovery Endpoint that enables a client application to automatically search for a discoverable service and find its address at runtime.|  \n  \n### Child Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<standardEndpoints>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/standardendpoints.md)|A configuration element that supplies a set of criteria used by a client application to search for a discovery service. Criteria can be grouped into search criteria (specifying what services you’re looking for) and find termination criteria (how long the search should last).|  \n  \n### Parent Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<standardEndpoints>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/standardendpoints.md)|Defines a standard endpoint that contains information to enable an application to function as a client program that can find the endpoint address dynamically at runtime.|  \n  \n## See Also  \n <xref:System.ServiceModel.Discovery.DiscoveryClientBindingElement>   \n <xref:System.ServiceModel.Discovery.Configuration.DiscoveryClientSettingsElement>","nodes":[{"pos":[12,60],"content":"&lt;discoveryClientSettings&gt; | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>discoveryClientSettings<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,48],"source":"&lt;discoveryClientSettings&gt; | Microsoft Docs"}]},{"pos":[358,389],"content":"&lt;discoveryClientSettings&gt;","linkify":"&lt;discoveryClientSettings&gt;","nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>discoveryClientSettings<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph>","pos":[0,31],"source":"&lt;discoveryClientSettings&gt;"}]},{"content":"Contains the settings needed by an application to participate in the service discovery process as a client.","pos":[390,497]},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>system.ServiceModel&gt;","pos":[504,526],"source":"\\<system.ServiceModel>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>standardEndpoints&gt;","pos":[529,549],"source":"\\<standardEndpoints>"},{"pos":[558,564],"content":"Syntax","linkify":"Syntax","nodes":[{"content":"Syntax","pos":[0,6]}]},{"pos":[1322,1345],"content":"Attributes and Elements","linkify":"Attributes and Elements","nodes":[{"content":"Attr